% if: executable(network-monitor)

Network Scanner

The [prgm]network-monitor[/prgm] command continuously scans your network for active hosts using nmap.

$ [prgm]network-monitor[/prgm]                       # Scan default network (192.168.1.0/24)
$ [prgm]network-monitor[/prgm] [arg-value]10.0.0.0/24[/arg-value]           # Scan specific subnet
$ sudo [prgm]network-monitor[/prgm] [arg]--top-ports[/arg] [arg-value]100[/arg-value]  # Port scan mode (requires root)

Options: [arg]--sort-by[/arg] (ipv4, ipv6, hostname, latest), [arg]-n[/arg] (no DNS lookup)
